I still like the pattern matching version, better. It's more concise, and I can actually follow it easier. (but my brain is weird):<p><pre><code>  def qsort[T <% Ordered[T]](list:List[T]):List[T] = {
    list match {
      case Nil => Nil     
      case x::xs =>        
        val (before,after) = xs partition (_ < x)
        qsort(before) ++ (x :: qsort(after))
    }
  }</code></pre>
